<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TolE0455">
<l>mutalī reṇṇiṉmu ṉuyirvaru kālait</l>
<l>tavaleṉa moḻipa vukarak kiḷavi</l>
<l>mutaṉilai nīṭa lāvayi ṉāṉa</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>It is stated that when a vowel appears before the first two numbers,</l>
<l>the sound <foreign xml:lang="ta">u</foreign> [of their modified forms] disappears, and the initial</l>
<l>[vowels] [occurring] there are lengthened.<note place="foot">I.e. <foreign xml:lang="ta">oṉṟu</foreign> and <foreign xml:lang="ta">
          iraṇṯu</foreign> the ' first two numbers ', loose the <foreign xml:lang="ta">-u</foreign>
          of their modified forms <foreign xml:lang="ta">oru</foreign> and <foreign xml:lang="ta">
          iru,</foreign> and their initial vowels are lengthened eg. <foreign xml:lang="ta">oṉṟu
          uḻakku &gt; oru + uḻakku</foreign> (by aphorism 446) &gt; <foreign xml:lang="ta">ōruḻakku.</foreign></note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
